NEWCASTLE DISEASE, TURKEYS - FINLAND: OIE
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 22 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Emergency Messages [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/040721SWE.htm>

Newcastle Disease in Finland
-------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of Newcastle disease in Finland reported to the
OIE: September 1996).
Information received on 20 Jul 2004 from Dr Riitta Heinonen, Deputy
Director General, Veterinary and Food Department, Ministry of Agriculture
and Forestry, Helsinki:
Date of the report: 20 Jul 2004.
An outbreak of Newcastle disease in a holding in Satakunta was laboratory
diagnosed. The infection was detected in routine screening in the holding
containing 12 000 fattening turkeys. No clinical signs have been seen.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 19 Jul 2004.
Estimated date of primary infection: 18 Jun 2004.
Diagnostic tests used: serology, virus isolation, RT-PCR.
Causal agent: paramyxovirus-1, intracerebral pathogenicity index=1.6.
Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
Control measures:
- All birds on the infected holding will be killed and destroyed.
- A protection and a surveillance zone have been established in accordance
with Directive 92/66/EEC of the Council of the European Communities. Trade
in live poultry and poultry products is prohibited from the protection and
surveillance zones.
--
